56/* This file contains a table of "standard" extensions */
57
58extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_bcons, v3_nscert, v3_key_usage, v3_ext_ku;
59extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_pkey_usage_period, v3_sxnet, v3_info, v3_sinfo;
60extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_ns_ia5_list[], v3_alt[], v3_skey_id, v3_akey_id;
61extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_crl_num, v3_crl_reason, v3_crl_invdate;
62extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_delta_crl, v3_cpols, v3_crld, v3_freshest_crl;
63extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_ocsp_nonce, v3_ocsp_accresp, v3_ocsp_acutoff;
64extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_ocsp_crlid, v3_ocsp_nocheck, v3_ocsp_serviceloc;
65extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_crl_hold, v3_pci;
66extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_policy_mappings, v3_policy_constraints;
67extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_name_constraints, v3_inhibit_anyp, v3_idp;
68extern const X509V3_EXT_METHOD v3_addr, v3_asid;
69
70/* This table will be searched using OBJ_bsearch so it *must* kept in
71 * order of the ext_nid values.
72 */
73
74/* TODO(fork): OCSP support */
75#define OPENSSL_NO_OCSP
76
77static const X509V3_EXT_METHOD *const standard_exts[] = {

79&v3_ns_ia5_list[0],

81&v3_ns_ia5_list[2],

83&v3_ns_ia5_list[4],
84&v3_ns_ia5_list[5],
85&v3_ns_ia5_list[6],
86&v3_skey_id,
87&v3_key_usage,
88&v3_pkey_usage_period,
89&v3_alt[0],
90&v3_alt[1],
91&v3_bcons,
92&v3_crl_num,
93&v3_cpols,
94&v3_akey_id,
95&v3_crld,
96&v3_ext_ku,
97&v3_delta_crl,
98&v3_crl_reason,
99#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_OCSP
100&v3_crl_invdate,
101#endif
102&v3_sxnet,
103&v3_info,
104#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_OCSP
105&v3_ocsp_nonce,
106&v3_ocsp_crlid,
107&v3_ocsp_accresp,
108&v3_ocsp_nocheck,
109&v3_ocsp_acutoff,
110&v3_ocsp_serviceloc,
111#endif
112&v3_sinfo,
113&v3_policy_constraints,
114#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_OCSP
115&v3_crl_hold,

117&v3_pci,
118&v3_name_constraints,
119&v3_policy_mappings,
120&v3_inhibit_anyp,
121&v3_idp,
122&v3_alt[2],
123&v3_freshest_crl,
124};
